{"cursor":"11148","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox astronaut |name =Richard Harrison Truly |image =Richard H. Truly - GPN-2002-\n000090.jpg |type =USAF/NASA Astronaut |status =Retired |nationality =American\n|birth_date = |birth_place =Fayette, Mississippi |occupation =Test Pilot |rank\n=Vice Admiral, USN |selection =1965 USAF MOL Group 1, 1969 NASA Group 7 |time\n=8d 07h 21m |mission =ALT, STS-2, STS-8 |insignia = }} 'Richard Harrison Truly'\n(born November 12, 1937) is a retired Vice Admiral in the United States Navy, a\nformer fighter pilot, former astronaut for both the United States Air Force and\nNASA, and was the eighth Administrator of the National Aeronautics and Space\nAdministration (NASA) from 1989 to 1992. He was the first former astronaut to\nhead the space agency.\n\nAfter his departure from NASA, he led the Georgia Tech Research Institute from\n1992 to 1997, and the National Renewable Energy Laboratory from 1997 to 2005.\n","linknr":379,"url":"Richard_H._Truly","recorded":1362267994,"links":48,"instances":["united_states","united_states","united_states"],"pdf":["http://foreign.senate.gov/testimony/2007/TrulyTestimony070509.pdf"],"categories":["1937 births","Living people","American astronauts","Administrators of NASA","United States Navy astronauts","United States Astronaut Hall of Fame inductees","People from Jefferson County, Mississippi","Georgia Institute of Technology alumni","U.S. Air Force Test Pilot School alumni","United States Navy admirals","United States naval aviators","Georgia Tech Research Institute people","Recipients of the Distinguished Service Medal (United States)","Recipients of the Legion of Merit","Recipients of the Distinguished Flying Cross (United States)","Recipients of the Meritorious Service Medal (United States)","Recipients of the Defense Superior Service Medal","Recipients of the NASA Distinguished Service Medal","Recipients of the NASA Exceptional Service Medal","Collier Trophy recipients",